Note: if you have closed the Inspector, secondary click on the object (in Desktop mode target the object and press CTRL+R), open your Context Menu (in Desktop mode: CTRL+T), and select "Open Inspector"
1.  Reselect the "Meshes (Scale Me)" object
2.  Create a child object
3.  Rename the child to "Hour Hand Pivot"
4.  Open Context Menu and select "Create New"
5.  Select "3D Model"
6.  Select "Box"
7. Secondary click on the Box
8. Open the Context Menu and select "Open Inspector"
9. Change the name to "Hour Hand"
10. Change the "Size" to ".08" (x), "0.5" (y), and "0.005" (z)
11. Click and drag the values from "Size" to "UVScale" for x, y and z to copy them
12. Scroll to the "Grabbable" component and deselect "Enabled".
13. Drag the "Hour Hand" slot into the "Hour Hand Pivot" slot
14. On the "Hour Hand" slot, click "Position" and "Rotation"
15. Set "Position" (y) to "0.25"
16. Set "Position" (z) to "-0.015"
17: Swap to the "Material Tool"
18: Select any material you like and click on the "Hour Hand" mesh to apply it
19: Swap back to the "Development Tool"
20: Click on the "Hour Hand Pivot" slot and on the "copy" icon to duplicate it
21: Double-click on the new "Hour Hand Pivot" slot and rename it to "Minute Hand Pivot"
22: Open up the slot and change the name of the new "Hour Hand" slot to "Minute Hand"
23: Change the "Size" on x to "0.05"
24: Copy the value of x on "Size" to the value of X on "UVScale"
25: Change the value of z on "Position" to "-0.02"
26: Swap tools and apply the material of your choice to the "Minute Hand" mesh
27: Select the "Minute Hand Pivot" slot and click on the "copy" icon to duplicate it
28: Double-click on the new "Minute Hand Pivot" slot and rename it to "Second Hand Pivot"
29: Open up the slot and change the name of the new "Minute Hand" slot to "Second Hand"
30: Change the Size on x to "0.03"
31: Copy the value of x on "Size" to the value of X on "UVScale"
32: Change the value of z on "Position" to "-0.025" (so you don't have to change it later)
33: Swap tools and apply the material of your choice to the "Second Hand" mesh
